data.chText: 我们现在的工作多半是承办婚宴。
data.enText: Most of our work now involves catering for weddings.
Who will be catering the wedding?

data.chText: 这个班对各种不同水平的人都适合。
data.enText: The class caters for all ability ranges.

tr: give what is desired or needed, especially support, food or sustenance
example: The hostess provided lunch for all the guests

value.def: In British English, to cater for a group of people means to provide all the things that they need or want. In American English, you say you cater to a person or group of people.

example.ex: Minorca is the sort of place that caters for families...
example.tran: 梅诺卡岛是那种适合家庭旅游的地方。

example.ex: We cater to an exclusive clientele.
example.tran: 我们只接待特定的高端客户。

value.tran: 为…提供服务;满足…的需要;接待

value.def: In British English, to cater for something means to take it into account. In American English, you say you cater to something.

example.ex: We have to cater for demand.
...shops that cater for the needs of men...
Exercise classes cater to all levels of fitness.
example.tran: 各种健身班会照顾到不同身体状况的人。

value.def: If a person or company caters for an occasion such as a wedding or a party, they provide food and drink for all the people there.

example.ex: Nunsmere Hall can cater for receptions of up to 300 people...
example.tran: 纳恩斯米尔酒店最多可以同时接待300人。

example.ex: The chef is pleased to cater for vegetarian diets...
example.tran: 厨师非常乐意为客人做素食。
他也承办派对的饮食吗？

value.tran: 为…提供饮食;承办…的酒席
